Many programming languages require that you provide bad code to the compiler
or interpreter. Due to limitations, you have to ensure that your code is in
certain lexical places to please the name resolution of the programming
language. The solution to this is to write nice code instead, and automate
the worsening. This technique is also known as literate programming.

Worsen has only one dependency: a Perl 5 interpreter. This makes it easy to
install and highly portable.
